01:02:38.736 --> 01:02:40.820
Kamil?

01:02:41.851 --> 01:02:43.934
What are you doing here?

01:02:44.019 --> 01:02:46.103
I came to see you.

01:02:47.152 --> 01:02:49.318
Did you write any good poetry?

01:02:51.074 --> 01:02:52.866
I haven't written since the crash...

01:02:53.225 --> 01:02:54.891
I work here.

01:02:55.473 --> 01:02:57.937
Pity, it's good material.

01:02:59.651 --> 01:03:01.151
But how?

01:03:02.153 --> 01:03:06.111
You've left the University?
Young Poland?

01:03:09.398 --> 01:03:11.398
And what about you?

01:03:12.391 --> 01:03:15.601
- Have you tested your theory?
- Which one?

01:03:16.968 --> 01:03:20.509
That Mercury is a moon of Venus...

01:03:20.915 --> 01:03:22.373
kicked away by a meteor

01:03:22.861 --> 01:03:25.861
and pushed into solar orbit...

01:03:26.653 --> 01:03:28.736
that's obvious.

01:03:32.008 --> 01:03:34.383
Why didn't you turn
onto the hard shoulder?

01:03:34.796 --> 01:03:37.197
He was coming straight at us.

01:03:58.729 --> 01:04:02.593
He should have turned,
he was in our lane.

01:04:04.703 --> 01:04:10.495
If we'd both turned off at the
same time even you'd be dead.

01:04:11.861 --> 01:04:13.945
I'd prefer that...

01:04:15.346 --> 01:04:16.513
I think.

01:04:16.734 --> 01:04:19.776
Yes. People are perfectionists.

01:04:20.499 --> 01:04:24.999
They love cleanliness,
order and final solutions.

01:04:25.473 --> 01:04:29.890
But luckily there's God
who makes mistakes.

01:04:30.539 --> 01:04:32.622
Night.

01:04:33.007 --> 01:04:35.007
Four in the morning.

01:04:36.293 --> 01:04:38.376
Silence everywhere...

01:04:40.029 --> 01:04:44.654
I hear a woman sobbing
behind the wall.

01:04:47.424 --> 01:04:49.049
No...

01:04:49.914 --> 01:04:52.748
I think she's laughing.

01:04:54.506 --> 01:04:55.922
Yes.

01:04:59.370 --> 01:05:02.120
I couldn't sleep last night.

01:05:03.350 --> 01:05:04.958
<i>It's impossible, I thought.</i>

01:05:05.043 --> 01:05:07.574
<i>Laughter can't sound
so similar to crying...</i>

01:05:07.954 --> 01:05:10.209
<i>they're opposites.</i>

01:05:11.381 --> 01:05:13.923
<i>Opposites are always
close to one another.</i>

01:05:14.269 --> 01:05:18.935
<i>So maybe in heaven they think
that we're always laughing.</i>

01:05:33.878 --> 01:05:36.392
<i>Air traffic over Europe
has been paralyzed.</i>

01:05:36.477 --> 01:05:40.476
<i>Clouds of volcanic dust are
drifting over from Iceland.</i>

01:05:40.709 --> 01:05:44.418
<i>According to experts, the ash
could cause engine seizures...</i>

01:05:44.584 --> 01:05:47.751
<i>The phenomenon of the volcanic dust,
which floats over Europe</i>

01:05:47.959 --> 01:05:50.293
<i>is extremely rare in our region,</i>

01:05:50.584 --> 01:05:53.992
<i>emphasises Grzegorz Sobczak,
editor of "Winged Poland".</i>

01:05:54.215 --> 01:05:55.249
<i>When will the dust settle?</i>

01:05:55.334 --> 01:05:57.372
<i>There are various forecasts,
because from what I hear</i>

01:05:57.543 --> 01:06:01.709
<i>the situation could sort
itself out in a day or two.</i>

01:06:01.833 --> 01:06:06.575
<i>In a critical situation we could wait
up to seven days for a change.</i>

01:06:06.955 --> 01:06:11.501
<i>The cloud might disrupt weekend memorial
ceremonies in Krakow and Warsaw.</i>

01:06:11.801 --> 01:06:14.626
<i>Yesterday 6000 flights were
canceled in Europe alone.</i>

01:06:14.787 --> 01:06:17.952
<i>Many transatlantic flights
were canceled as well.</i>

01:06:18.037 --> 01:06:20.949
<i>In spite of these difficulties, President
Barack Obama is still planning</i>

01:06:21.034 --> 01:06:24.600
<i>to travel to Poland for the funeral
of President Lech Kaczynski and his wife.</i>

01:06:24.926 --> 01:06:29.334
<i>The plan is that around 80 planes
will land at Krakow's airport</i>

01:06:29.543 --> 01:06:32.564
<i>with members of the delegations which will
participate in Sunday's funeral</i>

01:06:32.649 --> 01:06:34.709
<i>of the presidential couple.</i>

01:06:35.089 --> 01:06:37.959
<i>More bodies return to Poland.</i>

01:06:38.097 --> 01:06:40.959
<i>First came the plane with the body of
former president Ryszard Kaczorowski.</i>

01:06:41.168 --> 01:06:43.835
<i>The next one brought
34 coffins to Warsaw.</i>

01:06:44.122 --> 01:06:46.668
<i>Families waited at the airport.</i>

01:06:46.876 --> 01:06:48.543
<i>Prime Minister Donald Tusk says</i>

01:06:48.757 --> 01:06:53.175
<i>that Poland will remember the victims
of the tragedy and their legacy.</i>

01:06:53.449 --> 01:07:00.905
<i>We will carry on your dreams
of a better world, of truth.</i>

01:07:01.740 --> 01:07:07.126
<i>Each of you served
as best you could.</i>

01:07:08.024 --> 01:07:14.168
<i>We, as best we can, will
wish to hold up your legacy</i>

01:07:14.376 --> 01:07:18.043
<i>and carry it onward.</i>

01:07:18.855 --> 01:07:23.959
<i>If someone plants a bomb on a plane
you think, he's gonna say he did it?</i>

01:07:24.101 --> 01:07:27.168
<i>C'mon, what would they gain
exploding a bomb in a plane?</i>

01:07:27.272 --> 01:07:33.501
<i>What gain? The President and the most
important people in Poland were on it.</i>

01:07:33.834 --> 01:07:39.501
<i>Ruskies are guilty, they should give
all the documents, show everything...</i>

01:07:39.709 --> 01:07:42.043
<i>But they are covering it up,
showing nothing!</i>

01:24:31.349 --> 01:24:32.891
Do you hear?

01:24:33.349 --> 01:24:35.937
You need treatment.

01:24:41.391 --> 01:24:43.474
A priest came to see me.

01:24:45.099 --> 01:24:48.432
Listen, we're all worried
about you, understand?

01:24:50.016 --> 01:24:52.307
<i>We're worried.</i>

01:24:53.432 --> 01:24:56.266
<i>And answer that bloody
phone, will you?!</i>

01:25:08.654 --> 01:25:11.834
<i>O senseless strivings
of the mortal round!</i>

01:25:12.301 --> 01:25:18.433
<i>How worthless is that exercise of reason
that makes you beat your wings into the ground!</i>

01:25:19.057 --> 01:25:24.208
<i>One man was giving himself
to low, and one to aphorisms,</i>

01:25:24.555 --> 01:25:31.295
<i>one sought sinecures, and one to rule
by force or sly persuasion,</i>

01:25:32.000 --> 01:25:36.703
<i>one planned his business,
one his robberies,</i>

01:25:37.625 --> 01:25:41.917
<i>one, tangled in the pleasure
of the flesh, wore himself out,</i>

01:25:43.304 --> 01:25:45.259
<i>and one lounged at his ease,</i>

01:25:46.599 --> 01:25:50.425
<i>while I, of all such
vanities relieved</i>

01:25:51.498 --> 01:25:53.939
<i>hang high in Heaven
with my Beatrice,</i>

01:25:54.024 --> 01:25:57.056
<i>arose to glory,
gloriously received.</i>

01:25:58.766 --> 01:26:02.387
<i>When each had danced his circuit</i>

01:26:02.731 --> 01:26:05.142
<i>and come back to the same
point of the circle,</i>

01:26:05.328 --> 01:26:09.684
<i>all stood still, like votive
candles glowing in a rack.</i>

01:26:11.307 --> 01:26:16.554
<i>And I saw the splendor of the blazing
ray that had spoken to me...</i>

01:26:29.766 --> 01:26:33.396
<i>O sparkling essence
of the Holy Spirit!</i>

01:26:33.916 --> 01:26:36.568
<i>How instantly it
blazed before my eyes,</i>

01:26:36.653 --> 01:26:40.198
<i>defeating them with glory,
their function lost!</i>

01:26:41.724 --> 01:26:44.638
<i>But Beatrice let
herself appear to me</i>

01:26:44.723 --> 01:26:52.531
<i>so glad in beauty that the vision must lie
with those whose glory outdoes memory.</i>

01:26:53.367 --> 01:26:57.869
<i>From her I drew again the power
of sight and looked up,</i>

01:26:58.509 --> 01:27:03.725
<i>and I saw myself translated, with her
alone, to the next estate of light.</i>

01:27:04.883 --> 01:27:07.974
<i>I was made aware
that I had risen higher</i>

01:27:08.024 --> 01:27:10.880
<i>by the enkindled ardor
of the red star that glowed,</i>

01:27:10.965 --> 01:27:13.676
<i>I thought, with more
than usual fire.</i>

01:27:14.224 --> 01:27:18.796
<i>With all my heart, and in the tongue
which is one in all men,</i>

01:27:19.243 --> 01:27:22.332
<i>I offered God my soul
as offering for this new bliss.</i>

